   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Time Series Profiles\n",
    "\n",
    "Finding profiles in Time Series is a common task to perform. If time series are impacted by human activity it is generally a good idea to investigate if there is a weekly pattern on it.\n",
    "\n",
    "Time Series toolbox provides time grouper for `groupby` method and for this case the `weekly` grouper which maps all records to a hypothetic week located at the beginning of the year 1940. This hypthetic week is very convenient as it conserves day of week and order it from Monday 1st to Sunday 7th.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### Imports\n",
    "\n",
    "We import required packages:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.dates as mdates\n",
    "from odapi.connectors import Irceline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from odapi.settings import settings\n",
    "settings.logger.setLevel(40)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Dataset & Client\n",
    "\n",
    "We load the dataset we previously stored and create the Irceline client:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data = pd.read_pickle(\"dump/brussels_2014.pickle\")\n",
    "client = Irceline()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Week profiles\n",
    "\n",
    "To use time grouper, just reference the desired method to `groupby` and then aggregate: "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "p = data.groupby(client.weekly).mean()"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "**Note:** When dealing with data ranging over several month and having human footprint on it, keeping rack of Day Light Saving time is also important as it impact human activities. Handling records with Time Zone aware timestamps and correct timezone does the job."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "scales = client.scales()\n",
    "for k in ['NO', 'NO2', 'O3']:#p.columns.levels[2]:\n",
    "    axe = p.filter(regex='{}/'.format(k)).droplevel([1,2,3], axis=1).plot()\n",
    "    axe.set_title(\"Week Profile 2014\")\n",
    "    axe.set_xlabel(\"Time, $t$\")\n",
    "    axe.set_ylabel(\"Series, $x(t)$\")\n",
    "    axe.set_ylim(scales[k])\n",
    "    lgd = axe.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1), loc='upper left')\n",
    "    axe.grid(which='both', color='lightgray')\n",
    "    axe.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.DayLocator())\n",
    "    axe.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%a'))\n",
    "    #axe.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=90)"
   ]
